  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening and Integration of the Cacao Value Chain in Siuna and Rosita</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project builds on previous work with Uni&#xF3;n Nacional de Agricultores y Ganaderos, supporting the cultivation of cocoa in the  Regi&#xF3;n Aut&#xF3;noma del Atl&#xE1;ntico Norte of Nicaragua, one of the most impoverished and isolated areas in the country. The proposed project will directly benefit 200 farmers by:

(1) Increasing cocoa yields, and yields of associated crops through training, technical assistance, the use of LWR&apos;s Cocoa Tool Kit, and repopulation of existing cocoa areas;
(2) Improving market access for these farmers by enhancing cocoa collection, fermentation and marketing capacity of local cooperatives and centros de acopio through improvements in infrastructure and equipment, training in cocoa processing, exchange visits, and experimentation for improved cocoa quality in collaboration with The Hershey Company; and
(3) Strengthening the participation and leadership of women and youth in local cocoa farmer organizations by training them as community-based extension workers and supporting them to provide technical assistance to cocoa farmers.</narrative>
  </description>
